  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-white">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
    <div class="bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">How much English do I need for travel?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">A solid A2–B1 level is enough for most travel situations — roughly 1,500 active words and basic past/future tenses. You can reach it with 3–6 months of daily practice.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">App or tutor?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Both. Apps build vocabulary; tutors let you role-play real travel scenarios. Five to ten tutoring sessions before a trip make a real difference.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-2">Cheapest fast-track?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Duolingo free + See Guru's three free trial lessons + $5 pay-per-lesson sessions. Under $40 for a full month of serious prep.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

    <aside class="mt-12 mb-4 p-6 bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl">
